      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ATTACHMENT (2) broke from a standing start first up then had a tough draw last time. Much better served by this barrier and his fitness will be building so he may be ready to show more. DEUS EX NZ (4) looks close to a win having chased handy rivals to place in his last two appearances at this venue. Goes up in distance but finds a suitable assignment so could break through tonight. MULLUM HANK (5) hasn't been too far off the placings of late, finishing only 4.3m off the winner last week. Put together a string of wins earlier in the campaign, the last of them coming the last time he attempted this distance. Could find his way back into the winners' stall. DASHING (6) has won a trial since disappointing last time. Good winner at this circuit and distance prior so can bounce back.",
